    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Assuming your set contains the strings you want to remove, you can use <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Map.html#keySet%28%29\">the <code>keySet</code> method</a> and <code>map.keySet().removeAll(keySet);</code>.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><code>keySet</code> returns a Set view of the keys contained in this map. The set is backed by the map, so changes to the map are reflected in the set, and vice-versa.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Contrived example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Map&lt;String, String&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();\nmap.put(\"a\", \"\");\nmap.put(\"b\", \"\");\nmap.put(\"c\", \"\");\n\nSet&lt;String&gt; set = new HashSet&lt;&gt; ();\nset.add(\"a\");\nset.add(\"b\");\n\nmap.keySet().removeAll(set);\n\nSystem.out.println(map); //only contains \"c\"\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3273973,
      "reputation" : 6117,
      "user_id" : 2756574,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 89,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Jfwkl6k2.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Sebastian",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2756574/sebastian"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 12,
    "last_activity_date" : 1487100911,
    "creation_date" : 1487100911,
    "answer_id" : 42234698,
    "question_id" : 17675804,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just for the sake of completeness: </p>\n\n<p>As guessed <code>java.util.AbstractSet#removeAll</code> really iterates over all entries, but with one little trick: It uses the iterator of the smaller collection:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>if (size() &lt;= collection.size()) {\n    Iterator&lt;?&gt; it = iterator();\n    while (it.hasNext()) {\n        if (collection.contains(it.next())) {\n            it.remove();\n        }\n    }\n} else {\n    Iterator&lt;?&gt; it = collection.iterator();\n    while (it.hasNext()) {\n        remove(it.next());\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
