  "title" : "Remove multiple keys from Map in efficient way?",
  "body" : "<p>I have a <code>Map&lt;String,String&gt;</code> with large number of key values pairs. Now I want to remove selected keys from that <code>Map</code>. Following code shows what I did to achieve that.</p>\n<pre><code>Set keySet = new HashSet(); //I added keys to keySet which I want to remove. \n</code></pre>\n<p>Then :</p>\n<pre><code>Iterator entriesIterator = keySet.iterator();\nwhile (entriesIterator.hasNext()) {\n   map.remove( entriesIterator.next().toString());\n} \n</code></pre>\n<p>This is working fine. What would be the better approach?</p>\n"
